concept.definition: x < y means x is less than y.
x > y means x is greater than y.
x  ≤ y means x is less than or equal to y.
x ≥ y means x is greater than or equal to y.
x ≈ y means x is approximately equal to y.
x − y means the value is between x and y inclusive.

“Quantity sufficient” stands for the latin term “quantum satis” which means “as much as necessary” i.e. adding enough of a constituent to achieve a specific final volume or total weight. QS is a placeholder for an amount or volume which has to be “adjusted” by the given circumstances in a particular preparation.
x = y means x and y represent the same thing or value.
x ≍ y means x and y do not represent the same thing or value but are corresponding or virtually identical especially in effect or function.
